# Django from Jupyter Notebook

# Use Django & models in a jupyter notebook

1. make sure your venv is activated
2. restart your jupyter notebook kernel
3. run the following code in a cell

```python
import os
import sys

# add your django project directory to the sys.path
# if you installed your project with `django-admin startproject PROJECT .` 
# then you need to stop the path BEFORE the /PROJECT/ directory

os.chdir('/Users/devin/development/projects/_data-pipelines/data-pipeline-boxing/')

sys.path.append('/Users/devin/development/projects/_data-pipelines/data-pipeline-boxing/')

os.environ['DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE'] = 'PROJECT.settings'

# import django and settings
import django
from django.conf import settings
django.setup()

# Import your models
from scrapers.models import BoxrecSingleBoxer
```